			<p>Statement</p>
			<p>Recorded with: <persName ref="#ehri_et_berner_isaak">Berner Isaak</persName>, born: <date when="1909-06-18">18.6.1909</date> in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName></p>

			<p>On <date when="1941-07-01">July 1st, 1941</date>, the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germans</term> came to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName>. On <date when="1941-07-02">July 2nd</date>, an auxiliary
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html">Latvian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> troop was formed. They wore green
				armbands on their sleeves with a skull on. The first thing this auxiliary troop did was to stop Jews in the street, to humiliate them,
				to throw Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> out of their <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">apartments</term> and to force them to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556">Work</term> was done clearing up, where the aim was not so much that
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> was done, but much more to tyrannise
				the Jews. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-599" type="subject">Beards were pulled out</term>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> had their hair cut off, <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642">beaten</term> and kicked, the people stayed lying on
				the floor. On <date when="1941-07-03">July 3rd</date>, the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">apartments</term> of the Jews began to be <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345">ransacked</term>. On <date when="1941-07-06">July 6th</date>, all the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogues</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-646" type="subject">were set on fire</term>. I can testify under oath
				that many <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735">rabbis</term>, cantors, temple assistants
				and families that lived in the neighbourhood of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject"
					>synagogues</term> were forced into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-646" type="subject">burning
					synagogues</term> and suffocated and <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532"
					>burnt</term> alive. Shortly afterwards, the mass arrests began amongst the Jewish population. Over a short period, 3000-4000 Jews
				disappeared, I don’t know what happened to these people. All of the Jews that were still free had to register daily at the prefecture
				and were sent to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>, where they were – of
				course – tormented in the worst ways possible. At the beginning of <date when="1941-09">September</date>, Prefect <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_stieglitz_robert">Stieglitz</persName> – a repatriated <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">German</term> who had come back to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html">Latvia</placeName> – gathered all the leading Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and told them to form a Jewish committee.
				The members were the lawyer Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_eljaschow_michael">Eljachow</persName>, Dr. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_mincs_vladimir">Minz</persName>
				<note type="gloss">Uncertain, whether he means Vladimir Mincs.</note>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kaugert">Kaugert</persName>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_minsker">Winzker</persName>, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_blumenthal">Blumfeld</persName>. Their task was: arranging
				for the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173">relocation</term> of the Jews in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName> to the working-class suburb of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Letgaler</placeName>, an area where originally 3000-4000 had lived. In this cramped
				area, in the small, low <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">rooms</term>, 30-40,000
				people had to find <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">accommodation</term>. We had to
				give our <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">apartments</term> to the people moving out
				of the working-class area without any compensation, and were only allowed to take essentials with us that we could carry; special
				permission was needed if you wanted to take, for example, a cupboard with you. If it was a good piece of furniture, then the
				permission wasn’t granted. The <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173">relocation</term>
				had to be carried out by <date when="1941-10-15">October 15th</date>, the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="ghetto">ghetto</placeName> was then fenced in, surrounded by
					<term type="subject" ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html">Latvian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>, the Jews were segregated and the tragedy
				of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> began.</p>
			<p>Already in the first days, many Jews who only got too close to the fence were <q><term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term> attempting to <term type="subject"
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204">escape</term></q>. Shots were fired into windows that were
				supposedly the black-out was not good enough, many people <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">died</term> as a result. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489">Work commandos</term> left daily. Anyone who was halfway able to
				tried to avoid it, as returning to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>
				could be deadly. You were checked at the gate, searches were undertaken and most were beaten; <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were not spared. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Groceries</term> and essentials were supplied by 14
				shops, but the allocation got less and less every week. Security was provided by the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480">Jewish Police</term>. On <date when="1941-11-20">November
				18th</date>, it was arranged that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>
				would be <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623">evacuated</term> and everyone would be
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transferred</term> to a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term>. When Dr <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_eljaschow_michael">Eljachow</persName> asked what would happen to the old and the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292">sick</term>, an SA man named <persName ref="#ehri_et_schulze"
					>Schulze</persName> answered bluntly that anyone who was unable to march would be <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">shot</term>. We were allowed to take 20 kg of luggage with us. We
				believed that were really going to be taken to a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject"
					>work camp</term>.</p>
			<p>On <date when="1941-11-20">November 20th</date>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html"
					>Latvian</placeName> workers came and isolated a small section of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP018_02.jpg"
				/> We didn’t know why they had done it, but on <date when="1941-11-23">November 23rd</date>, all of the strong <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were forced into this isolated section. On
					<date when="1941-11-30">November 30th</date>, the <q>grosse Aktion</q> (big action) began. At 6pm, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and old people – with or without luggage
				– were <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642">driven out</term> of their <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">apartments</term>. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345">Blows</term>, <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345">kicks</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shooting</term>, <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">murder</term> were the tactics used to prompt the terrified people.
				People stayed on the streets for the whole night, until 6am, in the frost, <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569">hungry</term> and many poorly dressed. A group of 1000 people were
				marched on foot along the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Moskauer Strasse</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Moscow Street</placeName>) under the strict supervision of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>.</p>
			<p>Nobody was allowed to watch, even <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryans</term>
				weren’t allowed to look out of the window as shots were immediately fired. This <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623">evacuation</term> lasted until <date when="1941-12-09">December 9th,
					1941</date>. During this time, those of us in the isolated part of the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-56">ghetto</term> heard that Russian <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511">prisoners of war</term> were digging <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1321">pits</term> outside of town by Quadrat in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/455898/salaspils.html">Salasplis</placeName> and in the Bickernjaken woods. We couldn’t find out
				initially what they were for. We found out from farmers that lived nearby and from the statements of those who had been able to <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204">escape</term>: The <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transports</term> with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> (and also several <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> too) were forced to the <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1321">pits</term> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">mown down</term> with machine guns. The screaming and wailing of the
				poor victims was so harrowing, that many farmers on the immediate area couldn’t sleep for days. In this action, around 27,000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, around 3000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> between 1 and 13 years as well as
				4000-5000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> who were less able to work were
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">murdered</term>. The whole Aktion was led by
				General <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000196">Jeckeln</persName>, who was based in the Knight’s
				Hall in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName> with his accomplices, Dr <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000244">Lange</persName> and the SA man <persName ref="#ehri_et_schulze"
					>Schulze</persName>. To the character of General <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000196"
					>Jeckeln</persName> I want to add: when several Jews were sent to his house to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> for him, he didn’t like two of them. Out
				of nowhere he <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">shot</term> them. After the end of the
				Aktion, nearly 5000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and around 270 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> who had been able to <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262">hide</term> during the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623">evacuation</term> remained in the small isolated section of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. I was the <distinct
					type="camp_language">camp elder</distinct> at the time and got permission from the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">commandants</term> to bring the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> into a special block, and later other
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Latvia</placeName> came as well. There was a total of 500-600
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> in the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">women</term>’s block. The new <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">commandant</term> was called <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Obersturmführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_krause_kurt">Krauss</persName>, his assistant was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Scharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_roschmann_eduard">Roschmann</persName>. The <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term> was designated a barrack/<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term> and all the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">inmates</term> had to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> without rest. Three shops were set up and
				we received <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food rationing</term> cards, concerning
				goods, there was only that which was left over from the shops in the large <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. Almost everyone went to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> every day. The large <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> was taken over by a trust, and the
				property found there was sold in packages for 15 marks to the local population, whole wagons full of clothes were sent to <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germany</term> as winter assistance from the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html">Latvian</placeName> people. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS men</term> kept the best things for themselves.
				Three days after the annihilation action, 13-14,000 Jews from <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germany</term> (<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>) were brought to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> that we had cleared out. They were
				brought from <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germany</term> to Szirotowa in first
				and second-class carriages and given coffee there by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-286" type="subject"
					>nurses</term> from the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Red Cross</orgName>. They had been
				given permission to bring luggage with them from <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159"
					>Germany</term> and so arrived quite well-equipped. In Szirotowa they were sorted with blows and beatings. The <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> were mostly sent to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/455898/salaspils.html">Salaspils</placeName> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work</term>/<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">annihilation</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">camp</term>, some of the old people were <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">shot</term> in Szirotowa, the rest were brought as
				mentioned into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. All of their
				luggage was stolen and they lived from what they got from us. It was strictly forbidden, that we left the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term> and went into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>, and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">inhabitants</term> of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> were also not allowed to come into
				contact with us. We went to <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556">work</term> every day.
				Every Jew in the barrack <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term> had to deliver
				money, valuables, stocks and gold. We surrendered 115,000 marks and a fortune in gold, jewellery and diamonds. The <pb n="3"
					facs="EHRI-ET-JMP018_03.jpg"/> worth is difficult to estimate, but it was a fortune. Eight days later, the first two Jews were
				publically <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541">hanged</term> in the barrack <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term>. One was found to have 60 pfennigs and the
				other 1 mark. After the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">execution</term> was carried
				out, the Jews were ordered to carry out another collection of money, golds and valuables, as it was clear that not everything had been
				handed over. We immediately carried out another collection and raised 80,000 marks. As a personal gift for the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">Commandant</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_krause_kurt">Krause</persName>, we kept some diamonds, a gold clock and cigarette case to one side for him. It
				was said, that he refused the gift and threw it into the basket with all the other things. A constable said later, that <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_krause_kurt">Krause</persName> took enough things that he could live from them for 100 years.</p>
			<p>The <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541">hangings</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shootings</term> in the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term> hadn’t stopped; for every small infraction, someone had
				to pay with their <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">life</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">executions</term> by hanging had to be carried out by
				the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480">Jewish Police</term> who were left in the
				barrack <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName> carried out many arrests amongst us, especially from important
				businessmen or industrial people. These people disappeared and never came back. Within a year, 1000 Jews had been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> existed until <date>1943-06</date>.
				Thereafter, it was disbanded and we were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
					>housed</term> in groups at the companies that we were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
					type="subject">working</term> for, in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
					>barracks</term> and under stricter guard.</p>
			<p>Some of the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">people</term> were taken to the newly
				founded <q><placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-788">Kaiserwalde</placeName></q>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496">concentration camp</term> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName>. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832">Food</term> was quite scarce in the factory <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, but there was enough to keep you alive
				and not have to <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569">starve</term>. As the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russians</orgName> approached, we were taken to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">housed</term> in a <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496">concentration camp</term>.</p>

			<p>Statement copied from the original.</p>

			<p>Protokol opsala: <persName ref="#ehri_et_fischerova_marta">Marta Fischerová</persName></p>
